1.title: Look Closer
1.plot: Hannah arrives in Los Angeles and immediately bonds with Mark, a charming street fashion photographer. Little do they know, Mark's ex-muse Cleo, the manipulative and ruthless "queen" of fashion blogging, is trying to win him back.

2.title: Taking Steps
2.plot: Riding high on the hypes her first shoot received, Hannah hits up Mark for a second shoot. As those photos begin to rack up an impressive number of hypes, Mark's manipulative ex-muse Cleo begins to figure out what is "distracting" him.

3.title: Shrouded Path
3.plot: At Mark's urging, Hannah attends her first blogger party and gets a taste for all the perks that can come along with being the new "it girl". When Cleo invites her to do lunch sometime, Hannah is in heaven. But why can nobody know about it? Are Cleo's motives really pure of heart?

4.title: Boardwalk
4.plot: Hannah's brother Tony is beginning to become curious about why she never seems to be at school. And where are all these nice clothes and accessories coming from? Later at a private luncheon with blog queen Cleo, Hannah is introduced to a special "supplement" that will supposedly help her to keep her body shape.

5.title: Fashion Blog
5.plot: At the urging of Cleo, Hannah decides to go against type and incorporate a little elegance into her next shoot. Things get tense with Mark when Hannah suddenly decides to take a stronger hand with how she is shot. She is "the star" after all. Back at home, Hannah continues her regimen of "supplements" to keep her slim body shape, but her brother Tony can tell that something is not right.

6.title: Rooftop
6.plot: After falling out with Mark over their last shoot, Hannah is in need of a new photographer. Lucky for her Cleo knows just the right guy to shoot her next look. But Julius' methods are a bit unorthodox. When he tries to kiss her while they are editing photos, Hannah bites his lip and she starts to freak out. Thankfully Cleo has some juice to help calm her down... with extra pulp.

7.title: Extra Juice
7.plot: After narrowly escaping the nefarious clutches of Cleo and Julius the night before, Hannah and her savior Mark reconnect over a casual photoshoot in her yard. Later that night while Hannah is doing her homework, a very important and potentially life changing e-mail arrives. Who could it be from?

8.plot:

9.title: Journey
9.plot: After receiving a life changing email. Hannah has to decide if she's going to be serious about her blogging and how it's going to affect her school and family life.
